# Testing standards

- When fixing a bug, add or update a regression test that fails before the fix and passes after.
- Test behavior and edge cases, not implementation details.
- Keep tests deterministic - no reliance on real network, wall-clock time, or test order.
- Run the relevant test suite after changes and report the actual result. If tests fail, say so with the output.
- New features land with at least the core happy-path test plus the most important failure case.
